  <subsection xml:id="subsec-Units-of-measuring-distance">
    <title>Units of measuring distance.</title>
    <introduction>
      <p>
        Distance is the length of the space between two points. eg
      </p>
      <p>
        Distance from the  grade 7 classroom and the assembly, home to school, assembly to your school latrine and etc.
      </p>
      <p>
        The SI unit of measuring distance is <m>kilometres \, \text{and} \, metres</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
              Kilometres can be written as <m>km</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Metres can also be written <m>m</m>.

            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </introduction>


    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Converting-kilometres-into-metres">
      <title>Converting kilometres into metres</title>
      <p>
        The conversions are as follows;
      </p>
      <p>
        <m>1\, kilometre= 1\,000 \, metres</m>
      </p>
      <p>
        Similarly <m>1\,000 \, metres = 1\, kilometre</m>
      </p>
      <activity>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                The distance from Jerald's home to the school is <m>3\,km</m>.
                He walks to school and back every day. How many metres does 
                he walk every day?
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Estimate the following distances in kilommetres and convert 
                the estimated distance to metres.
              </p>
              <tabular halign="left" bottom="medium" left="medium" top="medium" right="medium">
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell>Description</cell>
                  <cell>Estimated distance in kilometres</cell>
                  <cell>Estimated distance in metres</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>a)</cell>
                  <cell>The distance from the school to the nearest shopping centure.</cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>b)</cell>
                  <cell>The distance from the classroom to the assembly ground.</cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>c)</cell>
                  <cell>The distance from the school to the nearest police station.</cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Share your work with other learners in your class.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </activity>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Convert <m>12\,km</m> to metres.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            If <m>1 \, kilometre = 1\,000 \, metres</m>
          </p>
          <p>
            Therefore, 
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 12 \, km = \amp (12 \times 1\,000)\, metres </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 12\,000 \, metres </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            Therefore, <m>12 \, km= 12\,000 metres</m>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Josphat cycled for <m>6.4 \, km</m>. How many metres did he cycle?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 1\, km=\amp 1\,000 \,m </mrow>
              <mrow> 6.4 \, km=\amp 6.4 \times 1 \, 000 \, m </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 6\, 400 \,m </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            Josephat cycled for <m>6\, 400 \, metres</m>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            The distance from Owilli's home to school is <m>4\frac{1}{2} \, km</m>. 
            How many metres is the school away from Owili's home? 
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 1\,km=\amp 1\,000 \, m </mrow>
              <mrow> 4\frac{1}{2} \,km=\amp 4\frac{1}{2} \times 1\,000\, m </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp  \frac{9}{2} \times 1\,000 \,m</mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp \frac{9\,000}{2}\,m </mrow>
              <mrow> = \amp 4\,500 \,m</mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            The distance from Owili's home to the school is <m>4\,500 \,m</m>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      
    </subsubsection>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Converting-metres-to-kilometres">
      <title>Converting metres to kilometres.</title>
      <p>
        As discussed above, the conversion of metres to kilometres is, <m>1\,000 \, metres= 1\, kilometre</m>
      </p>
      <activity>
        <p>
          Work in groups.
        </p>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                Grade 7 learners made the number cards below.
              </p>
              <sidebyside>
                <tabular halign="left" bottom="medium" top="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
                  <row>
                    <cell><m>1\,000\,m</m></cell>
                  </row>
                </tabular>
                <tabular halign="left" bottom="medium" top="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
                  <row>
                    <cell><m>3\,000\,m</m></cell>
                  </row>
                </tabular >
                <tabular halign="left" bottom="medium" top="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
                  <row>
                    <cell><m>4\,000\,m</m></cell>
                  </row>
                </tabular>
                <tabular halign="left" bottom="medium" top="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
                  <row>
                    <cell><m>10\,000\,m</m></cell>
                  </row>
                </tabular>
              </sidebyside>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Convert each of the above distance into kilometres
              </p>
              <p>
                Hint: <m>1\,000\,m=1\,km</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Share your work with other learners in class.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </activity>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Convert <m>17\,000\, m</m> to kilometres.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            Using the conversion formula that outlines, <m>1\,000\,m=1\,km</m>.
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 1\,000 \, m=\amp 1 km </mrow>
              <mrow> 17\,000m=\amp (17\, 000 \div 1\, 000)\,km </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 17\, km </mrow>
              
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            Therefore, 
          </p>
          <p>
            <m>17\,000\,m= 17 \, km</m>
          </p>
        </solution>

      </example>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            During a sports day, Murunga ran a distance of <m>3\, 700\,m</m>. 
            What distance did he cover in kilometres?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> 1\, 000\, m=\amp 1\,km </mrow>
              <mrow> 3 \, 700\,m =\amp (3\, 700 \div 1\, 000)\, km </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp (\frac{3\,700}{1\,000})\, km </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 3.7 \,km </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            Murunga coverd <m>3.7 \,km</m>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      
    </subsubsection>

  




    
