  <subsection xml:id="subsec-Speed">
    <title>Speed</title>

    <introduction>
        <p>
          Speed - is the total distance covered over the time taken in any activity done.
        </p>
        <p>
          The SI unit of measuring speed is kilometres per hour(<m>km/h</m>) or 
          metres per second(<m>m/s</m>).
        </p>
    </introduction>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Speed-in-kilometres-per-hour">
      <title>Speed in kilometres per hour (km/h).</title>
      <p>
        Speed is measured in <m>km/h</m>.
      </p>
      <activity>
        <p>
          Work in groups
        </p>
        <p>
          Go outside the classroom to the school's athletics field.
        </p>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                Take a walk outside the classroom and go to an athletics field.
              </p>
              <image source="/Field.png" width="40%">
                <shortdescription>(field)</shortdescription>
              </image>
              <p>
                One lap on the athletic field is <m>400\,m \, (0.4)\,km</m>
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Walk round the field one lap and record the time you take.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Run round the field once and record the time you take.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Run round the field two times and record the time you take.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Run round the field three times and record the time you take.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Fill the table below.
              </p>
              <tabular halign="left" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium" top="medium">
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell>Description</cell>
                  <cell>Distance in <m>km</m></cell>
                  <cell>Time taken in hours</cell>
                  <cell> <m>speed = \frac{distance}{time}</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>a)</cell>
                  <cell>Walking round the field once</cell>
                  <cell><m>0.4\,km</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>b)</cell>
                  <cell>Running round the field</cell>
                  <cell><m>0.4\,km</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>c)</cell>
                  <cell>Running round the field twice</cell>
                  <cell><m>0.8\,km</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>d)</cell>
                  <cell>Running round the field thrice</cell>
                  <cell><m>1.2\,km</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Share your work with other learners in your class.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
        <p>
          <em>LEARNING POINT</em>
        </p>
        <p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p>
                Speed is expressed in terms of distance covered per unit time.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li><m>Speed= \frac{distance}{time \, taken}</m></li>
            <li>Speed can either be expressed in kilometres per hour (<m>km/hr</m>) or metres per second (<m>m/s</m>).</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </activity>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            A truck travelled a distance of <m>240 \, km</m> in <m>4\, hours</m>. 
            What was its speed in kilometres per hour?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> speed= \frac{distance}{time} \amp </mrow>
              <mrow> Distance \,covered=\amp 240 \, km </mrow>
              <mrow>Time \,taken= \amp 4 \, hours </mrow>
              <mrow> Speed=\amp \frac{240 \, km}{4\, hours} </mrow>
              <mrow>  =\amp 60 \, km/h </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            The speed for the truck is, <m>60 \, km/h</m>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Akinyi walked a distance of <m>25\, kilometres</m> in <m>5 \, hours</m>.
            What was her speed in <m>km/h</m>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> speed=\amp \frac{distance}{time} </mrow>
              <mrow> Distance \, covered=\amp 25 \, km </mrow>
              <mrow> Time \, taken=\amp 5 \, hours </mrow>
              <mrow> Speed= \amp \frac{25 \, km}{5 \, hours} </mrow>
              <mrow> =\amp 5 \, km/h </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            Her speed was <m>5 \, km/h</m>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
     
    
      
    </subsubsection>


    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Speed-in-metres-per-second">
      <title>Speed in metres per-second(m/s)</title>
      <p>
        Speed can also be expressed in metres per second(<m>m/s</m>).
      </p>
      <activity>
        <p>
          Work in groups
        </p>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                Take a walk outside the classroom.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>Mark a distancde of <m>100\, m</m> in the field.</li>
            <li>Take turns to run the <m>100\, m</m> . </li>
            <li>Use a stopwatch to record the time taken by each learner in the group</li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Fill in the table below.
              </p>
              <tabular halign="left" bottom="medium" top="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
                <row header="yes">
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell>Name of the learner</cell>
                  <cell>Distance in metres</cell>
                  <cell>Time taken in sedconds</cell>
                  <cell><m>speed= \frac{distance}{time}</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>a)</cell>
                   <cell><m>100 \, m</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>b)</cell>
                   <cell><m>100 \, m</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <cell>c)</cell>
                   <cell><m>100 \, m</m></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                  <cell></cell>
                </row>
              </tabular>

            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Share your work with other learners in your class.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </activity>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Mark covered a distance of <m>100\,m</m> in <m>20\, seconds</m>. 
            What was his speed in metres per seconds?
          </p>
          <p>
            <m>Speed = \frac{distance covered}{time \, taken}</m>
          </p>
          <p>
            Distance he covered <m>=100\,m</m>, Time he took <m>20 \, seconds </m>
          </p>
          <p>
            Therefore,
          </p>
          <p>
            <md>
              <mrow> speed=\amp (100 \, m \div 20 \, seconds)</mrow>
              <mrow> = \amp (\frac{100}{20}) \, m/s</mrow>
              <mrow> \=amp 5 \, m/s </mrow>
            </md>
          </p>
          <p>
            Mark's speed is <m> 5 \, m/s </m>.
          </p>
          
        </statement>
      </example>
      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            A cyclist covered a distance of <m>200\,m</m> 
            in <m>2\, minutes </m>. What was his speed in <m>m/s</m>?
          </p>
        </statement>
